{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Jesus going up to Jerusalem took the twelve disciples apart in the way, and said unto them"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
         ,
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Jesus Predicts His Death"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 20,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then came to him the mother of Zebedee's children with her sons, worshipping him, and desiring a certain thing of him"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "A Mother's Request"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he said unto her"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Grant that these my two sons may sit, the one on thy right hand, and the other on the left, in thy kingdom",
          "speaker": "Mother of Zebedee's Children"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But Jesus answered and said"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "We are able",
          "speaker": "James and John"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when the ten heard it, they were moved with indignation against the two brethren"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But Jesus called them unto him, and said"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 29,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And as they departed from Jericho, a great multitude followed him"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 30,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And, behold, two blind men sitting by the way side, when they heard that Jesus passed by, cried out, saying"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Have mercy on us, O Lord, thou Son of David",
          "speaker": "Two Blind Men"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Healing Two Blind Men"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 31,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the multitude rebuked them, because they should hold their peace: but they cried the more, saying"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Have mercy on us, O Lord, thou Son of David",
          "speaker": "Two Blind Men"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 32,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Jesus stood still, and called them, and said"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 33,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Lord, that our eyes may be opened",
          "speaker": "Two Blind Men"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 34,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "So Jesus had compassion on them, and touched their eyes: and immediately their eyes received sight, and they followed him"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    }
  ]
}